HEADWORD: Edulcoration
<hw>E*dul`co*ra"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos> <ety>[Cf. F.
<ets>⟦eacute⟧dulcoration</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn> <def>The act of
sweetening or edulcorating.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <fld>(Chem.)</fld> <def>The act of freeing from acids or
any soluble substances, by affusions of water.</def> <mark>[R.]</mark>
<rj><au>Ure.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><-- p. 472 --></p>

<p><ent>Edulcorative</ent>⟦br⟧
